s_n?sec.<br /><br />"ts_[n]sec" _is_ a bit more intuitive, but it's WRONG. Strange but true, <br />it really _is_ supposed to be "tv_[n]sec" even for timespec. <br /><br />In short, you need to fix the pthreads library, not linux.<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
